Clinical Practice: The following events have been identified during postmarketing use of ketorolac tromethamine ophthalmic solution 0.5% in clinical practice.   Because they are reported voluntarily from a population of unknown size, estimates of frequency cannot be made.  The events, which have been chosen for inclusion due to either their seriousness, frequency of reporting, possible causal connection to topical ketorolac tromethamine ophthalmic solution 0.5%, or a combination of these factors, including corneal erosion, corneal perforation, corneal thinning and epithelial breakdown (see 
   PRECAUTIONS, General
).
